# Subagent TTS — Priority is Mandatory

Every speak call inside a Task subagent (explore / shell / generalPurpose) **MUST** include priority `1` and the `subagent` session. Subagents use the **young-sounding** sticky pool (Jenny, Aria, Michelle, Blue, Nancy — see `pick-session-voice.py`).

## Why this matters

Without priority, a subagent's TTS waits behind the global speak lock — **silent subagents**.

Priority `1` pre-empts competing TTS and speaks immediately.

## Required subagent speak pattern (copy verbatim into every Task prompt)

```bash
$OPENCLAW_HOME/scripts/oc-speak.sh "your message here" 1 subagent
```

## Test command

```bash
$OPENCLAW_HOME/scripts/oc-speak.sh "Subagent priority TTS test. If you hear this, the fix is working." 1 subagent
```

## Enforcement checklist

When writing any Task subagent prompt, verify:

- [ ] priority `1` (second argument)
- [ ] `subagent` as third argument

Missing either is a bug.
